Sentencas: Thin film solid oxide fuel cells with nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anodes deposited by sputtering were operated at 500 A degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: The fuel cells each have 750 nm-yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolytes and 200 nm-platinum cathodes.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: The thicknesses of the anodes are 240 nm, 320 nm, and 400 nm.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: The cell with the 320-nm-thick anode showed the highest maximum power density among all cells.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: Through electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, the anodic activation resistance and the ohmic resistance were calculated.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: The anodic activation loss decreased with an increase in the anode thickness.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: Therefore, the cell with the 400-nm-thick anode showed the lowest activation polarization resistance.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: Additionally, the ohmic resistance, the sum of various electronic/ionic resistances, was lowest when using the 320-nm-thick anode.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode

Sentencas: The electronic resistance and the ionic resistance of the anode were found to exist in a trade-off relationship owing to the current-collecting method of the anode.
Titulo: Characterization of thin film solid oxide fuel cells with variations in the thickness of nickel oxide-gadolinia doped ceria anode
